{"parse":{"title":"Permanent adjustments of theodolites","pageid":43579996,"revid":832350396,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The permanent adjustments of <a href=\"/wiki/Theodolite\" title=\"Theodolite\">theodolites</a> are made to establish fixed relationship between the instrument's fundamental lines. The fundamental lines or axis of a <a href=\"/wiki/Theodolite\" title=\"Theodolite\">transit theodolite</a> include the following:-\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Vertical_axis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vertical axis\">Vertical axis</a></li>\n<li>Axis of plate levels</li>\n<li>Axis of <a href=\"/wiki/Telescope\" title=\"Telescope\">telescope</a></li>\n<li>Line of collimation</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Horizontal_axis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Horizontal axis\">Horizontal axis</a></li>\n<li>Axis of altitude bubble</li></ul>\n<p>These adjustments once made last for a long time. These are important for accuracy of observations taken from the instrument. The permanent adjustments in case of transit theodolite are:-\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Horizontal axis adjustment</b>.</li></ul>\n<p>The horizontal axis must be <a href=\"/wiki/Perpendicular\" title=\"Perpendicular\">perpendicular</a> to the vertical axis.\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Vertical circle index adjustment</b>.</li></ul>\n<p>The vertical circle must read <a href=\"/wiki/Zero\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Zero\">zero</a> when the line of <a href=\"/wiki/Collimation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Collimation\">collimation</a> is horizontal.\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Adjustment of altitude level</b>.</li></ul>\n<p>The axis of altitude level must be <a href=\"/wiki/Parallel_(geometry)\" title=\"Parallel (geometry)\">parallel</a> to the line of collimation.\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Collimation adjustment</b>.</li></ul>\n<p>The line of collimation or line of sight should coincide with axis of the telescope.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The line of sight should also be perpendicular to the horizontal axis at its intersection with the vertical axis . Also, the <a href=\"/wiki/Optical_axis\" title=\"Optical axis\">optical axis</a> , the axis of the objective slide, and the <a href=\"/wiki/Sightline\" title=\"Sightline\">line of sight</a> should coincide.\n</p>\n<ul><li><b>Adjustment of horizontal plate levels</b>.</li></ul>\n<p>The axis of plate levels must be perpendicular to the vertical axis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Permanent_adjustments_of_theodolites&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Temporary_adjustments_of_theodolite\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Temporary adjustments of theodolite\">Temporary adjustments of theodolite</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Ranging_rod\" title=\"Ranging rod\">Ranging rods</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tape_(surveying)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tape (surveying)\">Tape (surveying)</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Permanent_adjustments_of_theodolites&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Surveying by Dr. B.C Punmia and Dr  Ashok Kumar Jain</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">surveying volume 1 by Prof. C.L Kochher, page no. 340 and 341.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2135\nCached time: 20180918142032\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.032 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.037 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 104/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 392/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 100/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 621/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.003/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 525 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   23.043      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   23.043      1 -total\n 12.85%    2.960      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:43579996-0!canonical and timestamp 20180918142031 and revision id 832350396\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Surveying"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Civil_engineering"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Collimation"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Horizontal axis"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Optical axis"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Parallel (geometry)"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Perpendicular"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Ranging rod"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Sightline"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Tape (surveying)"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Telescope"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Temporary adjustments of theodolite"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Theodolite"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Vertical axis"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Zero"}],"templates":[{"ns":10,"exists":"","*":"Template:Reflist"},{"ns":10,"exists":"","*":"Template:Main other"},{"ns":828,"exists":"","*":"Module:Check for unknown parameters"}],"images":[],"externallinks":[],"sections":[{"to